# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# people_directory scratch & derived artifacts — never inputs to the pipeline.
#
# Tracked (kept in the public repo): machinery only —
#   parse_raw.py, parse_extra.py, gen_directory.py, sync_vault.py,
#   sync_fellowships.py, qc_directory.py, regen_guard.py, WORKFLOW.md,
#   qc_metrics.csv (append-only trend log; invariant 10 needs cross-run
#   continuity).
#
# Untracked (all data lives in the private data repo, ahead of this repo
# going public — same rationale as extra_data.json + 01_data/ CSVs):
#   * Derived products: people.json, org_categories.json, notion_fellowships.json,
#     fellowships_to_create.json, dataset_info.json, missing_papers.json.
#   * Static Notion snapshot: notion_conferences.json (WORKFLOW.md L31; cloner
#     must repopulate from the data repo or re-scrape Notion).
#   * arxiv id→title cache: arxiv_titles.json (WORKFLOW.md L34; degrades
#     gracefully — missing ids fall back to a Scholar-search link).
#   * Dated one-off analyses: GAP_ANALYSIS_<date>.md (parallel to QC_REPORT_*.md).
#
# See WORKFLOW.md (sources-of-truth) + repo-root CLAUDE.md §7.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Underscore-prefixed analysis oneshots and their binary/JSON/HTML outputs
# (_louvain.py, _cluster_report.py, _X.npy, _graph.pkl, _communities.json,
# _REDESIGN_PREVIEW.html, …). CLAUDE.md §7: scratch scripts are never tracked.
# No tracked script or data file starts with an underscore, so this can't
# shadow a real file.
_*

# Regen-guard fingerprint cache — local debounce state, mirrors
# 01_data/index/source_state.json.
.regen_state.json

# Point-in-time weekly-QC reports — regenerated each run. The durable trend
# signal lives in qc_metrics.csv (tracked), cf. 02_logs/ run history ignored.
QC_REPORT_*.md

# Dated cluster/analysis dumps emitted by the _*.py oneshots (they hardcode a
# baked-in date; kept locally, out of git).
directory_analysis_*.html
people_*_20[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9].html
people_*_20[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9].csv

# Derived products that embed third-party data (researcher records, papers,
# fellowships, dataset stats). Regenerated by the pipeline (parse_raw.py /
# parse_extra.py / gen_directory.py) from vault + Notion sources; a cloner
# rebuilds them locally.
extra_data.json
ai-safety-people-directory.html
people.json
org_categories.json
notion_fellowships.json
notion_conferences.json
fellowships_to_create.json
dataset_info.json
missing_papers.json
arxiv_titles.json

# Dated gap/analysis reports (parallel to QC_REPORT_*.md above).
GAP_ANALYSIS_*.md

__pycache__/
.DS_Store
